{
  "texts": [
    "The analysis of peer assessment interactions and phenomena could benefit from social network analysis according to Djelil et al. (2021).",
    "They applied a graphlet-based method to a dataset collected during in-class courses integrating a peer assessment platform.",
    "Students developed a positive tendency towards adopting the peer assessment process and engaged gradually with well-balanced roles, even though initially they chose mostly to be assessed by teachers and more likely by peers they knew.",
    "Now we present a Case Study which aligns both with the areas of the Theoretical Framework and with the areas of the Scoping Review (although it only touches upon five of the six areas).",
    "Here we present a case study using a tool called RiPPLE (Khosravi et al., 2019) that transforms student learning into an active, personalized, and social journey."
  ]
}